Authorities around the world responded by implementing travel restrictions, quarantine, touchdowns, workplace hazard controls and facility closures.
The pandemic caused a severe global socio-economic disruption, the postponement or cancellation of sporting, religious, political and cultural events, and the widespread shortage of supplies aggravated by panic-driven purchases.
Schools and universities closed nationally or locally in 193 countries, affecting approximately 99.4% of the world’s student population.
