Antibacterial soaps have been promoted intensively for a health-conscious public.
Currently, there is no evidence that the use of the recommended disinfectants or antiseptics preserve antibiotic-resistant organisms by nature.
However, antibacterial soaps contain common antibacterial agents, such as triclosan, which has an extensive list of strains of resistant organisms.
